# FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (FRD)

## 1. Document Overview

### 1.1 Purpose
This Functional Requirements Document (FRD) translates the business requirements specified in the BRD for Use Case 1 into detailed, implementation-ready functional requirements for the AWS-based data processing pipeline. The system will ingest customer and order data from S3, perform data cleaning, implement SCD Type 2 logic using Hudi, and generate aggregated analytics.

### 1.2 Scope
This FRD covers:
- Ingestion of customer and order CSV files from AWS S3
- Data cleaning and deduplication processes
- Glue Catalog table registration
- SCD Type 2 implementation for order summary using Apache Hudi
- Incremental processing logic triggered by customer updates
- Aggregation table generation for customer spend analytics
- AWS infrastructure components for ETL, storage, cataloging, and querying

### 1.3 Source Document Reference
- **Source BRD**: Business Requirement Document – AWS Version
- **S3 Path**: s3://adif-sdlc/brd_usecase1/BusinessRequirementDocument_usecase1.pdf

### 1.4 Assumptions
- AWS Glue has appropriate IAM permissions to read from source S3 buckets and write to target S3 locations
- Apache Hudi framework is available and configured within AWS Glue environment
- Athena has access to query Glue Data Catalog tables
- CloudWatch is configured for monitoring Glue jobs
- CSV files in source locations follow the schemas defined in the BRD
- Date fields are in a format compatible with Spark/Glue processing (Not specified in BRD)

