### **FR-CLEAN-001: Remove Null Values from Customer and Order Datasets**
- **BRD Reference**: Section 3 (Data Cleaning)
- **Description**: The system shall remove records containing "Null" (string) and NULL (actual null) values from both customer and order datasets.
- **Inputs**: 
  - Customer DataFrame: CustId, Name, EmailId, Region
  - Order DataFrame: OrderId, ItemName, PricePerUnit, Qty, Date, CustId
- **Processing Rules**:
  - Identify records where any field contains the string "Null" (case-sensitive as specified)
  - Identify records where any field contains NULL value
  - Remove all such records from both datasets
- **Outputs**: 
  - Cleaned Customer DataFrame
  - Cleaned Order DataFrame
- **Preconditions**: Customer and Order DataFrames are loaded
- **Postconditions**: Datasets contain no "Null" strings or NULL values
- **Error Conditions**: Not specified in BRD

